China Agrees to End Wind Power Subsidies, USA Today Cites USTR

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-06-07T04:44:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/china-agrees-to-end-wind-power-subsidies-usa-today-cites-ustr.html
China  has agreed to stop subsidies to
wind power companies that choose domestic components instead of
imports under its “indigenous innovation” program, USA Today
reported, citing U.S. Trade Representative Ron Kirk.  The subsidies are valued at $6 million to $22 million, the
report said. The agreement comes seven months after the U.S.
started a probe based on a complaint from the United
Steelworkers, the article said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gregory Turk at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  